message.content:
1. Patients were randomized into three groups for a 1-year period.
2. Group 1 received follow-up eye care in a community-based setting.
3. Group 1 had assistance from a patient navigator.
4. Group 2 received follow-up eye care in an office-based setting.
5. Group 2 had assistance from a patient navigator.
6. Group 3 received follow-up eye care in an office-based setting.
7. Group 3 did not have assistance from a patient navigator.
8. Group 3's care was considered the usual care.

messages.content:
Statement: Patients were randomized into three groups for a 1-year period: Group 1 (G1) received follow-up eye care in a community-based setting with assistance from a patient navigator; Group 2 (G2) received follow-up eye care in an office-based setting with assistance from a patient navigator; and Group 3 (G3) received follow-up eye care in an office-based setting without a patient navigator (usual care).
